Title: 3) Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Situational Awareness                                                                   18.471      14.550          8.583
Description: This thrust area provides the necessary modeling, forecasting, and prediction capabilities to intelligently quantify
and visualize the impacts of chemical and biological (CB) agent exposures. These capabilities support real-time communication
and situational understanding to maintain lethality when the total force is operating in CB threat environments. Efforts under
this thrust area leverage data from other science and technology (S&T) programs to develop forecasting models and hazard
assessments to provide warfighters with optimal situational awareness in these environments. This thrust area is also enhancing
human machine integration by exploiting advances in eXtended Reality (XR), Virtual Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR) to
provide warfighters with an immersive environment for realistic training and mission rehearsal opportunities and will explore the
development of a digital human representation.

