Program/project is entering completion and all activities will be closed.
Title: 9) Employment Characterization                                                                                                          4.809       4.622          6.265
Description: Employment characterization provides the Chemical and Biological Defense Program (CBDP) with robust core
capabilities that provide the data necessary to refine threat assessments and potential impacts of indoor or outdoor releases of
CB threat agents on operations, strategy, and capabilities. Investments examine current and emerging technologies through the
lens of adversarial exploitation and inform potential gaps in CB defensive capabilities. The data from these efforts is critical for risk
assessments, hazard modeling, and operational decision making.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue studying employment methods & technologies at varying scale to include laboratory chamber, and field trials to
understand feasibility for adversarial use.

