Title: 3) Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Situational Awareness                                                               5.169       5.558        12.875
Description: This thrust area provides the necessary modeling, forecasting, and prediction capabilities to intelligently quantify
and visualize the impacts of chemical and biological (CB) agent exposures. These capabilities support real-time communication
and situational understanding to maintain lethality when the total force is operating in CB threat environments. Efforts under
this thrust area leverage data from other science and technology (S&T) programs to develop forecasting models and hazard
assessments to provide warfighters with optimal situational awareness in these environments. This thrust area is also enhancing
human machine integration by exploiting advances in eXtended Reality (XR), Virtual Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR)
in order to provide warfighters with an immersive environment for realistic training and mission rehearsal opportunities and will
explore the development of a digital human representation.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Initiate the enhancements of the Chemical and Biological (CB) Development, Security, and Operations (DevSecOps) digital
environment by advancing artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) based data analytics and automation to increase
the efficiency and rate at which modeling capabilities can be developed and enhanced.
- Continue to enhance the performance of Transport and Dispersion (T&D) models through the continuous integration of threat
data, for urban environments, and for hazard releases from novel platforms.

