Investment increases provides network support to enable improved coverage, protocols and decentralized data collection to
enable medical readiness and response.
Title: 2) Chemical Biological Incident Preparedness and Response - Model Development (CBIPR-MODEL) - Non-Clinical Testing                      4.404       4.878          4.635
Description: The Chemical Biological Incident Preparedness and Response Model Development (CBIPR-MODEL) program
delivers essential non-clinical testing articles at time of need to accelerate chemical and biological medical countermeasure
(MCM) development, and evaluates alternative sources (e.g. organoids, etc.) to reduce long-term reliance on non-clinical models
and to further mitigate the supply chain risks associated with availabilities.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue contract to support the purchase of nonclinical models at staggered intervals.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue to support the supply of essential non-clinical testing articles for pre-clinical models on an as needed basis to mitigate a
program's pre-clinical timeline.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to program shift from solely sourcing non-clinical testing articles to evaluating new alternative models to reduce
CBDP enterprise risk and reliance on traditional non-clinical models for MCM development.
