clinical model development and evaluation
Description: Organoid Development

FY 2027 Plans:
Transition and further develop organoid development and evaluation technologies to reduce the utilization of non-clinical models.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase transitions organoid technologies from Science and Technology to reduce risks and reliance on traditional non-
clinical models used for medical countermeasure development.
Title: 4) Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Defense Experimentation (CBRNDEX) - Integrated CBDP Experimentation                            -              -        9.578

                                                                                Defense Program - Dem/Val

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Description: Experimentation will provide touchpoints across the acquisition horizon to assess the value of CBDP capabilities in
development against operational concepts in the near-, mid-, and long-term. Experimentation will serve as a method to identify
requirements and acquisition solutions to shorten the time between gap identification and fielding. The CBDP Experimentation
and Prototyping Foundry will be an innovation and integration center for rapid development, assessment, acquisition, fielding and
integration of capability sets that allow the Joint Force to survive, fight and win in a CB-contaminated environment.

FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate a Foundry pilot to accelerate development of CBRN defense capabilities that address the operational needs of U.S. Indo-
Pacific Command and demonstrate the value of this integrated experimentation and prototyping concept. Funds the personnel,
equipment and other resources required to stand up a “minimum viable product” experimentation enabler that supports the
Enterprise’s capability development efforts.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
CBRNDEX focuses and expands existing experimentation and prototyping efforts.
Title: 5) Chemical Biological Radiological and Nuclear Defense Forward Element Experimentation and Prototyping (CBRND FE                     -              -        9.800
EXPP)
Description: The Chemical and Biological Defense Program (CBDP), in coordination with USINDOPACOM and other priority
theaters, will conduct experimentation, systems integration, and rapid prototyping activities for CBRN defense forward in theater to
accelerate delivery of CBRND materiel capabilities to the Joint warfighter.

FY 2027 Plans:
Design and execute rapid experiments for component validation with USINDOPACOM and CBRND unit and other applicable
stakeholders for subsystem and component validation, mature concepts of operations and concepts of employment and integrate
CBRND experimentation into Combatant Command field exercises. Experimentation efforts funded by this program in FY 2027
will primarily support material capability development required for biological deterrence in USINDOPACOM.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increased investment focuses and expands existing experimentation and prototyping efforts toward priority Areas of Responsibility
(AoR).
