Title: 7) Integrated Early Warning Manufacturing Optimization (IEW MFRO)                                                                     -              -       14.200
Description: The Integrated Early Warning Manufacturing Optimization (IEW MFRO) capability will modernize and mature
technology for manufacturing that provides chemical and biological (CB) threat-informed decision-making and enhances
operational readiness. IEW MFRO will enhance operations near-term for CBRN Unmanned Aerial System (UAS) capabilities,
with incremental opportunity for CBRN Unmanned Ground Vehicles (UGV) and other CBRN payload capable platforms. IEW
MFRO will integrate manufacturing hardware and software from multiple prototypes with data processed from complementary
US government (USG) intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) data streams, tools, and processes to enable a
unified framework for enhanced integrated early warning. IEW MFRO benefits the warfighter by enabling the manufacturing
of technologies that will increase combatant commander’s understanding of adversarial actions, create freedom of maneuver,
establish opportunities for cover, and ensure combat power is able to be maintained through conflict.

FY 2027 Plans:
Optimize manufacturing activities and integration of software with hardware assets. The initiative will provide multiple echelons
with real-time understanding of the adversarial threat information left of launch, support and enable Commanders to adopting
protective measures, optimize detection and characterization efforts, and ensure seamless coordination across the Joint Force
and with coalition partners.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

