Title: 8) Medical Countermeasures Manufacturing Optimization (MCM MFRO) - Biological and chemical manufacturing platforms                 19.234       8.050          8.536
Description: The Medical Countermeasures Manufacturing Readiness and Optimization (MCM MFRO) program delivers rapid
response capabilities through priority access at manufacturing sites and the optimization of multiple manufacturing efforts to
achieve rapid manufacturing of biological and chemical medical countermeasures for broad spectrum medical countermeasures.
The program supports DoW strategic capabilities via Medical Readiness by optimizing the manufacturing processes, and
bolstering U.S. industrial manufacturing bases that will enable and preserve warfighter operationally availability and lethality. MCM
MFRO investigates expeditionary production capabilities to further reduce the time to respond to a threat.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete subset of optimized manufacturing processes for multiple vendors.
FY 2027 Plans:
Conduct preparatory manufacturing runs to lead up to a full end-to-end current Good Manufacturing Production run to
demonstrate a 100-day manufacturing capability from sequence to drug product. Conduct Food and Drug Administration (FDA)
engagements to determine regulatory pathway for approval of platform technology for drug product development. Initiate
manufacturing optimization efforts for additional medical countermeasure (MCM) modalities to accelerate and improve readiness
against biological and chemical threats.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to support of FDA engagements and preparatory accelerations of 100-day manufacturing sprints to improve
readiness against biological and chemical threats.
