Title: 10) Rapid Response Sprint Advanced Development (RRS ADV)                                                                                  -              -        1.110
Description: RRS ADV supports the testing and demonstration of innovative processes and technologies across an integrated
medical countermeasure system. RRS ADV will demonstrate readiness and identify potential process and technology barriers
in the development of medical countermeasures (MCM) development against an unknown biological threat. RRS ADV benefits
the warfighter by demonstrating how the system improved readiness and adaptability to advance diagnostics and therapeutics at
operationally relevant speed and scalability against new and/or emerging threats.

FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate pre-planning activities to include a system-level tabletop exercise to assess current portfolio readiness and what aspects of
the capabilities will be demonstrated and tested in live fire event.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increased investment enables medical readiness and response through integrated systems and innovative processes and
technologies to identify potential process and technology barriers.
