Title: 2) Advanced and Emerging Threat Defense (AET DEFENSE)                                                                              7.105       7.167         7.980
Description: The AET Defense program addresses the highest priority chemical and biological (CB) gaps and supports the
Chemical Biological Defense Program (CBDP) Strategic Line of Effort to meet current, advanced, and emerging threats by
anticipating chemical, biological and toxin hazards and identifying capabilities to counter these threats. The AET Defense
program collaborates with the Joint Services and interagency to align RDT&E resources to determine readiness against threats as
they are identified across the entire CBDP enterprise portfolio.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continue efforts to address emerging chemical, biological, and other advanced threats. Maintain evaluation and assessment of
ability to detect and mitigate threats. Update hazard data management tools to incorporate emerging threat information. Conduct
yearly workshop on understanding advanced and emerging threat priorities to align with the CBDP. Conduct market surveys and
assessments of technologies for rapid fielding by the CBDP to mitigate emerging threat gaps as threats are identified.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue efforts to produce additional data to better assess detection, protection, and hazard mitigation capabilities against
chemical, biological, toxic, and other threats. Conduct workshops on understanding advanced and emerging threat priorities to
align with the CBDP. Conduct market surveys and assessments of technologies for rapid fielding by Chemical Biological Defense
Program to mitigate current, advanced, or emerging threat gaps as needed.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Minor change due to routine program adjustments.
