Title: 6) Genomic Enabled Sequencing (GENOMES)                                                                                               -              -           2.350
Description: The Genomic Enabled Sequencing (GENOMES) effort facilitates integrated and layered genomic sequencing efforts
across the Chemical and Biological Defense Program (CBDP) portfolio for the Joint Force. GENOMES will provide threat agnostic
identification of current, emerging, and engineered biowarfare agents. GENOMES will support development of automated sample
preparation, bioinformatic software and databases, and diagnostic workflows and procedures. GENOMES efforts will enable
production and delivery of new capabilities and technology insertion and product improvement of existing systems. GENOMES
benefits the warfighter as an overarching portfolio enabler for integrated genomic layered defense, providing both hardware and
software that unencumber the warfighter, accelerate sample-to-answer times, and simplify lifecycle logistics.

FY 2027 Plans:
Investigate methods to identify toxins, fungi, and agnostic unknown biological threat agents using genomic sequencing. Areas
of development will include both wet laboratory protocols and bioinformatics/data analysis. Funds will also cover the quality
assurance and quality control of consumables from commercial vendors, to ensure compatibility with systems being fielded
under Programs of Record. Funds will support the enabling sequencing efforts across the CBDP, to include shelf-stabilization
of reagents requiring cold storage. Funds will support Market Research - Automated Sample Preparation. Fund program
management and administration processes to include but not limited to program oversight, resource justification, budgeting and
programming, and schedule tracking.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increased investments enable integration of sequencing capabilities across existing efforts.
Title: 7) Multi Phase Chemical Sampling and Analysis (MPCSA)                                                                                 -              -           0.348
Description: The Multi-Phase Chemical Sampling and Analysis (MPCSA) will provide a man-portable analytical two-dimensional
(2D) mass spectrometer that will conduct real-time, near-laboratory grade analysis of solid, liquid, and vapor samples collected
by an operator in a contaminated area. This will provide field confirmatory identification and classification capability for unknown
chemical threat agents. MPCSA benefits the warfighter by providing Commanders with a higher fidelity analysis of samples
collected in the field than the currently fielded detectors for maneuver, protection, decontamination, and treatment measures.

FY 2027 Plans:
Begin developmental testing on prototypes transitioned from Science and Technology (S&T). Complete necessary requirements
for successful Milestone A decision planned in fourth quarter FY 2027. Begin Program management and administration

