Title: 11) Non-targeted Sequencing Identification System (NSIS)                                                                               1.715             -               -
Description: The Non-Targeted Sequencing Identification System (NSIS) provides a rapid biological sequencing capability to
identify known, emerging, engineered, enhanced biological warfare agents (BWA), and endemic pathogens of concern. NSIS
allows for the detection of genetically engineered agents near the point of attack, reducing potential exposure and increasing
opportunity for containment. The NSIS capability will increase the Joint Force's ability to identify agents beyond those currently
targeted by fielded equipment, providing early warning of a potential outbreak or attack and informing decisions to protect the
Homeland and Joint Force Missions. NSIS benefits the warfighter by enabling untargeted analysis on-site to provide actionable
intelligence to the Chain of Command at the speed of relevance.

