 capability. The AET Defense program will utilize OTAs for system development and prototyping activities and Government Agencies and Federally Funded Research
 and Development Centers to provide testing and technical support.

 Colorimetric Indicator (CIND)

 CIND is an Approved Acquisition Category (ACAT) IV program anticipated to enter into acquisition following receipt of draft service requirements and the transition from
 science and technology. The acquisition strategy will use an incremental acquisition approach starting with a Commercial Off-the-Shelf (COTS) capability set, with future
 capability sets utilizing Science and Technology (S&T) solutions. The program will work with the CBDP S&T partner and will use the Combating Weapons of Mass
 Destruction Other Transactional Authority (CWMD-OTA) project agreement to transition technologies from Science and Technology (S&T) to Acquisition.

 Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Support to Command and Control (CSC2)

 CSC2 is executed through the Software Acquisition Pathway, leveraging existing Information Technology Box requirements and Capability Needs Statements (CNS)
 furnished through the Services and Combatant Commands. CSC2 is executing a modular contracting approach, where the use of Other Transaction Authorities (OTAs),
 and Indefinite Delivery/Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) will be used to meet agile software objectives of continuous development, integration, delivery, and engineering. CSC2
 will establish a Service and Combined Joint All-Domain Command and Control (CJADC2) compatible chemical and biological (CB) Common Operating Environment
 (COE) architecture and leverage existing enterprise Develop Security Operations (DevSecOps) efforts to facilitate continuous and iterative delivery of capability to the
 Joint Force through the development of a unified software solution.

 Far Forward Biological Sequencing (FFBS)

 FFBS will employ an incremental strategy to field capability quickly, with Increment 1 using manual sample preparation of Deoxyribonucleic Acid (DNA) on target,
 Increment 2 automating sample preparation of DNA and Ribonucleic Acid (RNA) on target, and reducing sample to answer times. FY 2027 BA4 funding for Increment 2
 supports continued prototype testing of up to two promising S&T performers under Technology Transition Agreement# 26-FFBS-25-001T.

 Genomic Enabled Sequencing (GENOMES)

 GENOMES will use an agile acquisition strategy to support multiple capability sets, supporting development and fielding of solutions at the speed of relevance. Efforts
 will support development of technologies transitioned from science and technology partners as well as exploring Commercial off-the-Shelf (COTS) and Government off-
 the-Shelf (GOTS) systems.

 Multi Phase Chemical Sampling and Analysis (MPCSA)

 MPCSA program will utilize Countering Weapons of Mass Destruction (CWMD) Other Transaction Authorization (OTA) project agreement funded in partnership with
 Science and Technology (S&T) to evaluate prototypes prior to and then complete technology transition. Follow on acquisition contract will also leverage either the Broad


