- CB Decontamination/Hazard Mitigation (estimated funding, $2.6 Million): Advance development of portable, on-demand
capabilities for decontamination of chemical warfare agents.
- CB Physical Protection (estimated funding, $3.8 Million): Improve respiratory protection (e.g., breathing apparatus, filters) to
protect the warfighter from chemical biological (CB) threats.
- CB Warning and Decision Support (estimated funding, $2.0 Million): Initiate development of a tactical tool/capability to increase
situational awareness and enhance decision support of Warfighters operating in CB-contested environments.
- CB Medical Diagnostics (estimated funding, $3.7 Million): Initiate efforts for shelf-stable diagnostic tests capable of rapid
