Title: 5) Weapons of Mass Destruction Civil Support Teams (WMD CST)                                                                     1.707       1.477          2.049
Description: The Weapons of Mass Destruction Civil Support Teams (WMD CST) supports the fielded system upgrade and
ongoing assessment and acquisition of Commercial Off-the-Shelf (COTS) and Government Off-the-Shelf (GOTS) analytical
detection, protection, decontamination and sampling equipment for survey in order to expand/enhance the operational capabilities
of the WMD CST. WMD CST benefits the warfighter by actively monitoring the currently fielded National Guard Bureau (NGB)
equipment and establishes a time phased modernization roadmaps to integrate and incorporate proven advancements in
commercially available technology into the NGB mission set based on highest priority capability requirements and availability of
resources.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete testing efforts for Next Generation Physiological Status Monitor Testing, and Man-Transportable Robotic System.
Complete Unmanned Aircraft System sensor integration effort, and conduct down select for Next Generation Mass Casualty
Decontamination. Begin market research for Rebreather and respiratory protection efforts. Continue program management and
administration processes to include but not limited to program oversight, resource justification, budgeting and programming, and
schedule tracking.
FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate Unmanned Aircraft System Tether Testing. Finalize Rebreather and respiratory protection down select efforts. Begin the
market research on next generation chemical detection capability to replace the MultiRAE. Continue program management and
administration processes to include but not limited to program oversight, resource justification, budgeting and programming, and
schedule tracking.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding increase supports scope of engineering support and testing requirements for planned activities.
