Remarks

D. Acquisition Strategy
Chemical Biological Radiological Nuclear Support to Command and Control (CSC2)

 The acquisition strategy uses a capability portfolio management approach to drive development, engineering, and modernization of Integrated Early Warning (IEW).
 CSC2 employs a System of Systems methodology to iteratively enhance capabilities while maintaining existing MOD CBRN IS systems for cybersecurity and bug
 fixes until replaced. New modular and interoperable CSC2 products will enhance CBRN situational awareness and integrate into a Continuous Integration/Continuous
 Delivery (CI/CD) pipeline, ensuring operational relevance and adaptability to mission needs. The contracting strategy is aligned with this acquisition strategy, supporting
 modular, iterative development (following a consistent quarterly capability release schedule) and ensuring flexibility to deliver capabilities efficiently while maintaining
 cybersecurity and sustainment for existing systems.

