($1.324) Continue development of (1) Fiber Optic Return Loss Standards multi-mode calibration hardware
standard in electro optical (multi-mode) measurement technology to support shipboard readiness of weapon
system communication to missile launch systems, combat Flight operations and ground combat operations.
Multimode fiber optics significantly contributes to operational efficiency, information security, and communication
reliability. Begin development of (1) Fiber Optic Time-of-Flight System Upgrade to support shipboard Readiness
of Weapon System communication to Missile Launch Systems. Capability supports main data communications
on the U.S. Navy's surface ships and submarines. Continue development of (1) High Energy Laser Beam
Profiler standard supporting combat and operational Readiness. Capability will ensure superior performance
and lethality when applied in various military scenarios, such as targeting, surveillance, and weapon systems.
Continue development of (1) LiDAR 3D Scanner Calibration standards to reduce cost and turnaround time
for critical ship building areas including damage, repair, maintenance, and modification assessment. Begin
development of (1) 3D Printer Measurement Standards and Processes for Automated Parts Qualification whose
performance is vital to the production of on-demand replacement parts. This effort provides timely and efficient

