Operational Systems Development$$, $$The Defense Counterintelligence and Security Agency (DCSA) is a strategic asset to the nation and our allies - continuously ensuring a trusted federal, industrial, and
affiliated workforce and enabling industry's delivery of uncompromised capabilities by leveraging advanced technologies and innovation. DCSA uniquely blends critical
technology protection, counterintelligence, security and professional education and certification to advance and preserve America's strategic edge.

 DCSA Counterintelligence (CI) conducts activities to identify, assess, deter and mitigate foreign intelligence and cyber threats to U.S. Government’s industrial base, the
 trusted workforce, and the cleared National Industrial Base (NIB).CI provides direct support to the National Industrial Security Program (NISP) and the cleared Defense
 Industrial Base (DIB) to ensure the safety of classified information from foreign adversaries. CI provides functional services to Department of War (DoW) and cleared
 industry.

 The CI Systems Modernization requires the capability to operate within a secure cloud infrastructure with Cross-domain Data Layer functionality. This modernization
 addresses critical capability gaps where Foreign Intelligence Entity (FIE) capabilities currently outpace CI’s legacy systems due to the sheer volume of information
 (32,000+ raw reports annually). The program requires Secure Data Ingestion, Advanced Data Analytics, and interoperability with DoW and National Intelligence systems.
 These features will enable CI to triage reporting in real-time, automate records retention, and integrate Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) to confront
 an evolving threat landscape.

