FY 2027 Plans:
In FY 2027, CI delivers advanced analytical capabilities building upon the FY 2026 infrastructure. This includes the full integration
of Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) tools for automated data mining, predictive analysis, and statistical
modeling. Efforts will focus on multi-nodal network analysis, generating finished intelligence products with automated citation and
sourcing, and expanding interoperability with external government and industry data sets via secure application programming
interface. The system will support real-time decision-making and prescriptive analytics to anticipate foreign intelligence threats
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
This effort was funded under a different program in FY2026 and transferred to this program in FY2027. The increase reflects
the progression from initial infrastructure acquisition and core system development (Cloud/Cross-Domain setup) into the
deployment of advanced software capabilities (AI/ML integration) and steady-state sustainment. Funding is required to maintain
the accelerated development timeline ensuring CI incorporates new critical capabilities by the end of fiscal year 2026 to mitigate
identified risks to the Defense Industrial Base.
