A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Defense Counterintelligence Security Agency (DCSA) is a strategic asset to the nation and our allies - continuously ensuring a trusted federal, industrial, and
affiliated workforce, and enabling industry's delivery of uncompromised capabilities by leveraging advanced technologies and innovation. DCSA uniquely blends critical
technology protection, trusted personnel vetting, counterintelligence, and professional education and certification to advance and preserve America's strategic edge.

 The Polygraph+/Polygraph Next program is a transformative effort to modernize federal polygraph and credibility assessment technologies, enhancing accuracy,
 reliability, usability, and traceability. DCSA will conduct independent validation studies, field testing, and prototype evaluations to advance standoff sensing, automated
 scoring, and decision aids. The program also aims to develop centralized data storage and analytics capabilities to support these innovations. By integrating non-contact
 sensing systems and AI/ML-based scoring algorithms, Polygraph+/Polygraph Next will address emerging challenges in personnel vetting and insider threat detection,
 ensuring the integrity of the cleared workforce and safeguarding sensitive information critical to national security.

 This program is vital to national security, directly impacting the readiness of the warfighter by increasing efficiencies in vetting the trusted workforce. Standoff sensing
 capabilities, such as non-contact physiological monitoring, reduce variability in sensor setup, streamline workflows, and enable faster, more accurate assessments.
 These advancements minimize human error, improve traceability across cases, and enhance decision-making processes, ensuring that personnel vetting aligns with
 operational needs and readiness requirements. By modernizing credibility assessment technologies, Polygraph+/Polygraph Next strengthens the Department of War’s
 ability to maintain a trustworthy workforce, directly supporting mission-critical operations and safeguarding national security. Through collaboration with research
 partners like Applied Research Lab for Intelligence and Security (ARLIS), Oak Ridge National laboratory (ORNL), and industry leaders, Polygraph+/Polygraph Next
 delivers validated tools and methodologies that align with evolving mission needs and bolster the nation’s security posture.

