FY 2026 Plans:
Provide continued system development and enhancement for the NISS, NISP Contract Classification System (NCCS) 2.0, and
FY 2020 NDAA Section 847 Beneficial Ownership applications. Activities will include integration of multiple data sources and
enhancements to risk assessment and analytic capabilities. Support the continuous delivery of secure, automated, IT capabilities
for the DCSA Industrial Security Directorate to enable effective entity vetting, risk identification, and mitigation for cleared and
uncleared industry operating in the DIB. Develop and integrate new data sources for Facility Risk Management System (FRMS) in
support of FOCI compliance.

Provide Tier 3 help-desk resources to meet increased user demand following go-live of DFARS-driven FOCI workflows as part of
the NISS Increment II (NI2) Minimum Viable Capability Release (MVCR). Finalize workflow development, system integration, go-
live activities, and post-deployment help-desk support for NCCS. The NCCS workflow development includes incorporation of key
capabilities such as query and reporting tools, Certificate Pertaining to Foreign Interests (SF-328) interface, and other mission-
critical automation features. Complete account/case/workflow documentation management for NISS, and initiate refactoring of
legacy NISS workflows into NI2.
