The increase of +$16.000 million from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is required to rapidly develop and deploy a GCCS-J software version
capable of exchanging data with the Machine-assisted Analytic Rapid-repository System (MARS) being fielded by the DIA. DISA
must replace connections to the sunsetting Military Intelligence Integrated Database (MIDB) in time to allow the user community to
migrate prior to March 2028.
