(USW(P&R)). RDT&E funds are applied to research security and standards compliance improvements for the Common Access Card (CAC) and the Uniformed Services
Identification (USID) card, which provides identification for personnel not eligible for the CAC and for dependents. Funding for the Identity Credential Management (ICM)
program supports the DoW Chief Information Officer’s Identity, Credential and Access Management (ICAM) initiatives and the modernization of the identity management
and credentialing systems.$$, $$The Defense Human Resources Activity (DHRA) is a Department-wide Field Activity chartered to support the Under Secretary of War for Personnel and Readiness
(USW(P&R)). RDT&E funds are applied to research security and standards compliance improvements for the Common Access Card (CAC) and the Uniformed Services
Identification (USID) card, which provides identification for personnel not eligible for the CAC. In FY 2025, 2.4M CACs and 1.8M USIDs were issued. Expecting similar
rates of issuance through FY 2027. Funding for the Identity Credential Management (ICM) program supports the DoW Chief Information Officer’s Identity, Credential
and Access Management (ICAM) initiatives. DoW faces critical and escalating security and compliance risks due to its reliance on an outdated identity and access
management system. Urgent investment in a modern, Commercial Off The Shelf (COTS) based system is paramount to eliminating this vulnerability, ensuring robust
cybersecurity, streamlined access, and full adherence to critical federal mandates.

 Modernization will provide DoW with a commercial identity service that leverages modern algorithms—including Algorithm Evolution (AE) capabilities delivered through
 a web-based, cloud-native Next Gen Solution. This transition will yield measurable cost efficiencies, enhance the user experience, and align with strategic objectives.
 Furthermore, it will reduce IT complexity and significantly strengthen the security posture.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025           FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Identity Credential Management                                                                                                         9.192             8.798         8.988
Description: Identity and Credential Management establishes DHRA/Defense Manpower Data Center (DMDC) as the Enterprise
Identity and Credential Registration Service Provider for the Department of War. In this role, DMDC will develop improved identity
federation solutions for Identity and Credentialing programs including CAC and Uniformed Services ID cards.

FY 2026 Plans:
In FY 2026, DMDC will continue to demonstrate and evaluate CAC issuance from the modernized solution for compliance with
latest security standards. The CACs issued from the modernized solution will be evaluated to ensure access requirements are
satisfied.
FY 2027 Plans:
In FY 2027, DMDC will continue to evaluate, develop and test the modernized credentialing platform with the customer
assessment process.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

                                                                             urity Initiative

