the value of key policy and technology topics that connects to the successful return of absentee balloting materials from military
and overseas citizen voters pursuant to the Uniformed and Overseas Citizens Absentee Voting Act (UOCAVA). FVAP regularly
reaches out directly to 1.3 million active duty service members, and attempts to assist the estimated 700,000 military spouses and
dependents of voting age. FVAP also attempts to reach out to and assist the estimated 2.8 million overseas citizens of voting age.

